{
  "text": "In order to account for the 'skewed' propagation and to satisfy the cylindrical boundary conditions with m = 0 we need to consider a more complicated mode called a hybrid mode [CITATION_1] . When a light ray moves along a helical path, the polarization changes due to the interaction with the walls and we cannot have a solution with one pure polarization. This limitation does not appear in twodimensional propagation.",
